&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMPANY OVERVIEW:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Kitchen&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;brings together a range of disciplines and capabilities. It’s a team of creatives, producers, data analysts and social experts working together to deliver remarkable ideas that live in a variety of mediums, from everything from social to TV. This team moves at the speed of culture. It is built to respond to trends and events as they happen, coming up with the ideas that transcend social media to capture the spirit of the moment, earn media impressions, and get the country talking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Are you ready to join an award-ambitious team that&#39;s making waves in the advertising industry? Our incredible team has been recognized internationally by industry giants like Cannes, One Show and was named Campaign&#39;s Global ‘In-House Agency of The Year’, further solidifying our position as a leader in the industry. Join us and be a part of something truly special - a team that&#39;s dedicated to creating ground-breaking work and pushing limits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;At The Kitchen, we&#39;re not just looking for individuals who want to be a part of the advertising industry - we&#39;re looking for trailblazers who are ready to lead the way to the next big thing! We want individuals who are passionate about producing award-winning work and have an innate drive to their craft and are eager to generate innovative ideas both within and outside of the brief.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE OVERVIEW:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Associate Creative Director (Art) at The Kitchen, you’ll support the creative director to help lead a team of talented creatives to craft and write culturally resonant campaigns. Working alongside another ACD (Copy), you’ll collaborate with a diverse group of experts to craft ideas that move people and generate buzz. Whether it&#39;s a quick-turn trend activation or a thoughtfully crafted TV spot, you’ll be at the forefront of shaping work that captures attention, earns media, and inspires action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Creative:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;development and execution of campaigns, ensuring ideas are fresh, culturally relevant, and aligned with client objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Management:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Mentor and inspire a team of jr. art directors, copywriters, and content creators, fostering a collaborative and innovative environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trend Responsiveness:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Stay attuned to cultural and social trends, leveraging insights to deliver timely, impactful campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Partner with producers, strategists, data analysts, and social media experts to craft ideas that work seamlessly across platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Engagement:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Present concepts to clients with clarity and passion, building trust and enthusiasm for the work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Craft Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Ensure the highest standards of creative execution across all deliverables, from social-first content to integrated campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Award Ambition:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Drive the team to produce award-worthy work that sets industry benchmarks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EXPERIENCE &amp;amp; SKILLS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;7+ years of experience in a creative role within an agency or in-house team, with a track record of producing high-quality, award-winning work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Proven ability to lead, mentor, and inspire creative teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;s

&lt;p&gt;Craft &amp;amp; Commerce (C&amp;amp;C) is an integrated media agency that connects growth science, media strategy, and modern measurement to help our partners create greater marketing impact and grow with confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;C&amp;amp;C is purpose-built to bring a marketer’s mentality to today’s dynamic media landscape. The result is an expert, senior-level team that approaches media not as an agency, but as a business stakeholder committed to one thing: helping our partners outshine the competition through smarter, more agile planning and buying. Our secret sauce is the marriage of marketing effectiveness science and business impact measurement, together guiding us in balancing brand and performance, and translating data into actionable media strategies and hands-on campaign management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced &lt;strong&gt;Sr. Retail Media Search Associate &lt;/strong&gt;to manage and optimize paid search campaigns across retail media platforms. The ideal candidate will have&lt;strong&gt; hands-on expertise in Walmart Connect, Roundel Media Studio and Amazon Ads sponsored product and sponsored brand advertising,&lt;/strong&gt; along with deep knowledge of keyword strategy, campaign pacing, and reporting. A Skai Certification is required, demonstrating advanced skills in retail search management and optimization.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And at C&amp;amp;C—we treasure a candid, ask-the-right-questions, get-it-done attitude that’s at the heart of our fast-moving and collaborative team culture. We’re a flexible, balanced, self-driven workplace. The right candidate will join us remotely from a place that makes you happy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Planning &amp;amp; Activation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop retail media and growth plans tied to client goals and category trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build media and operational tactics based on those plans, launching campaigns across &lt;strong&gt;Walmart&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Target&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Amazon&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Campaign Execution &amp;amp; Optimization&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead hands-on campaign management: daily budget pacing, keyword bidding, placement adjustments, and bid-strategy refinements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use consumer behavior data and top-of-search tactics to refine paid search strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting &amp;amp; Insights Delivery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver regular performance reporting—monthly, quarterly, and mid-year—highlighting key business trends and category influences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Distill insights from data using Excel or Google Sheets to craft optimization recommendations for e-commerce outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor marketplace events (e.g. holiday trends, category promotions) and track their impact on campaign performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Engagement &amp;amp; Coordination&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present campaign trends and strategy to clients; participate in calls and internal alignment meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clear project prioritization and ensure all deliverables are coordinated and on-time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional partners (analytics, creative, account management) to sync search efforts with broader media strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of direct experience managing paid search campaigns for Walmart Connect, Target Roundel, and Amazon Ads (Sponsored Products + Sponsored Brands).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skai Certification is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Excel/Google Sheets—able to analyze large datasets, identify trends, and present findings.&lt;/li&gt;
