&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;Salt XC is an agency driven by Experiential Commerce™ — our unique framework for designing consumer experiences that earn attention and drive action. We connect a brand’s online and offline world through data, media, and memorable moments that move people.&amp;nbsp;We’re&amp;nbsp;one of the fastest-growing agencies in North America, and the people who thrive here are curious, energetic, and excited by the work.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;THE OPPORTUNITY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:100}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;This role is a genuine launchpad for someone who wants to build a career in advertising and experiential marketing. As Office Experience &amp;amp; Events Coordinator,&amp;nbsp;you’ll&amp;nbsp;sit at the&amp;nbsp;centre&amp;nbsp;of Salt’s Toronto office — keeping it running, making it feel alive, and playing a real part in how we show up for our team and our clients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;You’ll&amp;nbsp;work closely with our Facilities Manager, Executive Assistant, and Sr. Director of Operations to own the day-to-day of the office and support the events and moments that define Salt’s culture. From managing the rhythm of a busy creative office to helping produce internal events and client gatherings,&amp;nbsp;you’ll&amp;nbsp;get hands-on exposure across the business and build relationships at every level.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data

&lt;p data-start=&quot;152&quot; data-end=&quot;205&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;152&quot; data-end=&quot;203&quot;&gt;ROLE: RETAIL MEDIA STRATEGY MANAGER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;207&quot; data-end=&quot;244&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;207&quot; data-end=&quot;242&quot;&gt;TEAM: CRAFT &amp;amp; COMMERCE - MEDIA STRATEGY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;246&quot; data-end=&quot;294&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;246&quot; data-end=&quot;292&quot;&gt;LOCATION: UNITED STATES - REMOTE&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT CRAFT &amp;amp; COMMERCE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Craft &amp;amp; Commerce (C&amp;amp;C) is an integrated media agency, purpose-built to serve as a nimble, strategic partner to marketing teams in navigating our rapidly evolving media landscape. We fuse leading-edge performance marketing capabilities with a holistic view of channels, bring clarity to measurement and attribution across the funnel, and deliver scalable, ad-driven growth. Our expert team has stood in the shoes of our clients and sees media through the lens of larger business objectives. We combine this human touch with best-in-class technology and a suite of services focused on one thing: continually driving better results through media.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a &lt;strong&gt;Retail Media Strategy Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to lead &amp;amp; manage a portfolio of retailer relationships for one of our largest accounts. This is a leadership role responsible for developing media strategies &amp;amp; campaign plans and leading projects across multiple stakeholders. The Retail Media Strategy Manager will also be responsible for managing some day to day client relationships, budget tracking/pacing and aggregating reports.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the AVP of Media Strategy, the Retail Media Strategy Manager will ensure partner satisfaction via the stewardship of media strategy, campaign planning, vendor management, and communications between internal &amp;amp; external teams. Ideal candidates have experience in retail media, within a brand, agency or network and can act as a liaison, translator and champion between our client partners and vendors. Past experience in consumer brands is a plus, especially with emerging brands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll partner closely with client teams, platform leads, analytics, and media execution specialists to ensure we bring clarity, consistency, and strategic insight to every campaign in the planning, execution, and reporting stages. This is a high-impact, high-visibility position ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of media strategy, storytelling, and data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And—at C&amp;amp;C—we treasure a candid, ask-the-right-questions, get-it-done attitude that’s at the heart of our fast-moving and collaborative team culture. We’re a flexible, balanced, self-driven workplace. The right candidate will join us remotely from a place that makes you happy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CORE RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the planning, execution, and reporting of retail media campaigns across a variety of networks, primarily within Walmart Connect&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan for annual, quarterly and campaign-specific initiatives, as directed by client’s priorities throughout the year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring day to day success of both managed service and self service campaigns, including on time delivery, correct placements/audiences and client-directed KPIs are met&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;

