&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMPANY OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded by architects of the industry, Encore is one of Canada’s most respected field sales organizations, delivering selling, merchandising, technology, and strategic consulting solutions to tier-one clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Encore’s vision is to be the first choice for organizations seeking to optimize their field sales investment. Its mission is to provide uncompromising quality of service and unparalleled caliber of thinking—developing strategies and delivering solutions that enable clients to win .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;As part of the broader Tracxtion ecosystem, this role mirrors the structured, strategic, and values-led talent framework used across Traxction, ensuring consistency, scalability, and excellence in hiring practices.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As &lt;span class=&quot;collapsed-field-text&quot;&gt;Sr. Talent Acquisition Partner &lt;/span&gt;at Encore, you will drive the end-to-end talent acquisition strategy and execution for Encore’s national business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will lead full-cycle recruitment for priority and complex roles while overseeing and developing a small but high-impact recruitment team. You will partner closely with Encore business leaders and report into the Senior Director of Talent at SALT XC to ensure alignment with enterprise-wide talent standards, reporting, employer brand, and inclusive hiring practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role blends strategic leadership with hands-on execution. You will act as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A trusted advisor to Encore leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A people leader and coach to your team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A recruitment strategist who builds scalable, forward-thinking pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A champion of candidate experience and employer brand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bilingualism (English/French) is considered an asset, particularly for Quebec-based hiring, but is not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
